		"easy-crescent-veggie-pizza": {
			"name": "Easy Crescent Veggie Pizza",
			"difficulty": "Medium",
			"instructions": "Ingredients:\n2 cans (8 oz each) Pillsbury refrigerated crescent rolls <i>or</i> Pillsbury refrigerated crescent dough sheet\n1 package (8 oz) cream cheese, softened\n1/2 cup sour cream\n1 teaspoon dried dill weed\n1/8 teaspoon garlic powder\n1/2 cup small fresh broccoli florets\n1/3 cup quartered cucumber slices\n1 plum (Roma) tomato, seeded, chopped\n1/4 cup  shredded carrot\n\nStep 1: Heat oven to 375 degrees Fahrenheit\nStep 2: If using <b>crescent rolls:</b> Unroll both cans of dough; separate dough into 4 long rectangles. In ungreased 15x10x1-inch pan, place dough; press in bottom and up sides to form crust.\nIf using <b>dough sheets:</b> Unroll both cans of dough. In ungreased 15x10x1-inch pan, place dough; press in bottom and up sides to form crust.\nStep 3: Bake <b>13</b> to <b>17</b> minutes or until golden brown. Cool completely, about <b>30</b> minutes.\nStep 4: In small bowl, mix cream cheese, sour cream, dill and garlic powder until smooth. Spread over crust. Top with vegetables. Serve <b>immediately</b>, or cover and refrigerate <b>1 to 2 hours</b> before serving. Cut into 8 rows by 4 rows.\n<i> To easily soften cream cheese, remove wrapper and place on a microwaveable plate. Microwave uncovered on <b>High</b> for <b>15 to 20 seconds</b> or until softened.</i>",
			"tags": [],
			"footnote": ""
		},
		"crock-pot-potato-soup": {
			"name": "Crock Pot Potato Soup",
			"difficulty": "Hard",
			"instructions": "Ingredients:\n1 30oz. bag frozen diced hash browns\n1 32oz. box chicken broth\n1 can cream of chicken soup\n1 pkg. cream cheese\n3 oz. bacon bits\n1 cup shredded cheese\nSalt and pepper\n\nPut hash browns in crockpot. Add chicken broth, cream of chicken soup, and half of bacon bits. Add pinch of salt and pepper.  Cook on low <b>7-8 hours</b> or until potatoes are tender. An hour before serving, cut cream cheese into small cubes. Place in crockpot. Stir a few times throughout the hour before serving. Once cream cheese has melted, it's ready! Top with cheddar cheese and more bacon bits.",
			"tags": ["Soup"],
			"footnote": ""
		}
	},
